        term: "Weight of Money",
        definition:
          "Weight of money describes the amount of money being placed on different outcomes. It can influence odds movement, especially in exchange markets.",
      },
      {
        term: "Win Bet",
        definition:
          "A win bet is a bet on a selection to win the event or market. It is the simplest form of betting in many sports.",
      },
      {
        term: "Winning Margin",
        definition:
          "Winning margin is a market based on how much a team or player wins by. For example, a football team to win by exactly one goal.",
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    letter: "Y",
    items: [
      {
        term: "Yankee",
        definition:
          "A Yankee is a multiple bet involving four selections. It contains 11 bets: six doubles, four trebles and one four-fold accumulator.",
      },
    ],
  },
];

const letters = terms.map((group) => group.letter);
---

<MainLayout
  title="Betting Jargon Explained"
  description="A plain-English A-Z glossary of betting terms, odds jargon, bookmaker margin, hedging, dutching, lay betting, accumulators, each-way betting and betting maths phrases."
>
  <section class="content-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Betting glossary</p>
    <h1>Betting Jargon Explained</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A plain-English A-Z guide to betting terms, odds jargon and betting maths phrases, including accumulators, each-way bets, overround, dutching, hedging, lay betting, bookmaker margin, back/lay betting and implied probability.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Quick note:</strong> Betting terms can sound more complicated than they really are. This glossary explains the language and links key maths terms to our calculators where useful.
    </div>

    <div class="glossary-tools">
      <label class="search-box">
        <span>Search betting terms</span>
        <input id="glossary-search" type="search" placeholder="Search terms such as acca, each-way, lay bet, overround, SNR, liability..." />
      </label>

      <nav class="letter-nav" aria-label="Glossary letters">
        {letters.map((letter) => (
          <a href={`#letter-${letter}`}>{letter}</a>
        ))}
      </nav>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Popular betting maths terms</h2>
    <p>
      Some betting phrases are especially important for understanding how odds and markets work. These are the terms most closely linked to the Betting Maths calculators.
    </p>

    <div class="featured-grid">
      <a class="featured-card" href="/calculators/overround-calculator/">
        <h3>Overround</h3>
        <p>Calculate bookmaker margin and book percentage.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="featured-card" href="/calculators/dutching-calculator/">
        <h3>Dutching</h3>
        <p>Split a stake across two or more selections.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="featured-card" href="/calculators/hedge-bet-calculator/">
        <h3>Hedging</h3>
        <p>Work out back and lay hedge stakes.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="featured-card" href="/calculators/back-lay-calculator/">
        <h3>Back/Lay</h3>
        <p>Calculate lay stake, liability and commission.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="featured-card" href="/calculators/lay-liability-calculator/">
        <h3>Lay Liability</h3>
        <p>Understand your exchange betting exposure.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="featured-card" href="/calculators/accumulator-calculator/">
        <h3>Accumulator</h3>
        <p>Multiply odds and calculate acca returns.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="featured-card" href="/calculators/each-way-calculator/">
        <h3>Each-Way</h3>
        <p>Calculate win, place and losing outcomes.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="featured-card" href="/calculators/odds-converter/">
        <h3>Implied Probability</h3>
        <p>Convert odds into percentage chance.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>A-Z betting terms glossary</h2>

    <div id="no-results" class="no-results" hidden>
      No matching betting terms found. Try a broader search such as “odds”, “stake”, “lay”, “acca”, “each-way” or “margin”.
    </div>

    <div class="glossary-list">
      {terms.map((group) => (
        <section class="letter-section" id={`letter-${group.letter}`}>
          <h2>{group.letter}</h2>

          <div class="term-grid">
            {group.items.map((item) => (
              <article class="term-card" data-term={`${item.term} ${item.aka ?? ""} ${item.definition}`}>
                <h3>
                  {item.term}
                  {item.aka && <span>{item.aka}</span>}
                </h3>
                <p>{item.definition}</p>
                {item.link && <a href={item.link}>{item.linkText}</a>}
              </article>
            ))}
          </div>
        </section>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Why betting jargon matters</h2>
    <p>
      Understanding betting jargon is not just about knowing slang. Terms like overround, implied probability, lay liability, commission, stake not returned, each-way terms and value bet describe the actual maths behind betting markets.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you understand what the terms mean, it becomes easier to read odds, compare markets, use calculators correctly and avoid misunderstanding what a bet can return.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Responsible note:</strong> Learning betting terminology can help you understand risk, but it does not guarantee profit. Betting always involves risk, and you should only bet what you can afford to lose.
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .article-section {
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .glossary-tools {
      display: grid;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1.4rem;
    }

    .search-box {
      display: block;
      padding: 1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
    }

    .search-box span {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
      color: var(--color-navy);
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .search-box input {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 0.8rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      color: var(--color-text);
      font: inherit;
      background: white;
    }

    .search-box input:focus {
      outline: 2px solid rgba(31, 138, 91, 0.22);
      border-color: var(--color-green);
    }

    .letter-nav {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.45rem;
    }

    .letter-nav a {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-width: 38px;
      height: 38px;
      padding: 0 0.6rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: white;
      color: var(--color-navy);
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .letter-nav a:hover {
      background: var(--color-green);
      border-color: var(--color-green);
      color: white;
    }

    .featured-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .featured-card {
      display: block;
      padding: 1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
    }

    .featured-card:hover {
      border-color: rgba(31, 138, 91, 0.45);
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }

    .featured-card h3 {
      margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
    }

    .featured-card p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--color-muted);
    }

    .glossary-list {
      display: grid;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .letter-section {
      scroll-margin-top: 92px;
    }

    .letter-section > h2 {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      width: 46px;
      height: 46px;
      margin: 0 0 0.8rem;
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: var(--color-navy);
      color: white;
      font-size: 1.35rem;
    }

    .term-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .term-card {
      padding: 1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: white;
    }

    .term-card h3 {
      margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
    }

    .term-card h3 span {
      display: inline-flex;
      margin-left: 0.35rem;
      padding: 0.12rem 0.45rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: #eef8f3;
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      vertical-align: middle;
    }

    .term-card p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--color-muted);
    }

    .term-card a {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: 0.75rem;
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .term-card[hidden],
    .letter-section[hidden] {
      display: none;
    }

    .no-results {
      margin: 1rem 0;
      padding: 1rem;
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: #fff7e6;
      color: #8a5a00;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    @media (max-width: 980px) {
      .featured-grid {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 760px) {
      .featured-grid,
      .term-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    const searchInput = document.getElementById("glossary-search");
    const termCards = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll(".term-card"));
    const letterSections = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll(".letter-section"));
    const noResults = document.getElementById("no-results");

    function filterGlossary() {
      const query = searchInput.value.trim().toLowerCase();
      let visibleCount = 0;

      termCards.forEach((card) => {
        const text = card.dataset.term.toLowerCase();
        const matches = !query || text.includes(query);

        card.hidden = !matches;

        if (matches) {
          visibleCount += 1;
        }
      });

      letterSections.forEach((section) => {
        const visibleCards = section.querySelectorAll(".term-card:not([hidden])");
        section.hidden = visibleCards.length === 0;
      });

      noResults.hidden = visibleCount !== 0;
    }

    searchInput.addEventListener("input", filterGlossary);
  </script>
</MainLayout>
